# Generated JSON Schemas — `make schemas` rewrites these from Pydantic
# models using json.dumps. Letting Prettier reformat them would cause
# spurious diffs on every regeneration. They are still under gitleaks and
# tracked in git as the schema-versioning contract (CLAUDE.md §11, §38).
packages/shared-schema/schemas/

# Phase 04 — `scripts/export-redaction-rules.py` writes this verbatim
# from the Python source. Prettier reformat = drift = CI failure.
packages/shared-schema/redaction-rules.json

# Phase 03 report goldens — written by the Python writers via json.dumps
# with sort_keys + indent=2 (or by xml.etree). Prettier must NOT reformat
# them; the byte-for-byte comparison is the contract that detects schema
# drift. `make update-goldens` is the only sanctioned way to regenerate.
tests/golden/

# Phase 14 — `tests/integration/scoring/expected/` holds byte-locked
# replay goldens for the scoring pipeline. Same contract as tests/golden/.
tests/integration/scoring/expected/

# Phase 16 — SDK API snapshot. Regenerated by `make sdk-api-snapshot`
# via Python `json.dumps(sort_keys=True, indent=2)`. Prettier must NOT
# reformat it; CI compares the committed bytes against a live dump.
packages/python-sdk/api-snapshot.json

